      <description>&lt;p&gt;I am a PhD student in Agricultural &amp;amp; Resource Economics at &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.ualberta.ca/resource-economics-environmental-sociology/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Department of Resource Economics &amp;amp; Environmental Sociology&lt;/a&gt; at University of Alberta.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;My research aims to better understand decision making by examining behavioral responses to incentives and information with a focus on choices. My current research focuses on individuals&amp;rsquo; non-market behavior and the use of incentives to increase public good contributions. I typically use a microeconomics framework and applied econometric methods to model human behavior, test hypotheses, and develop policy recommendations.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I am on the 2019-2020 job market. Feel free to contact me at &lt;a href=&#34;mailto:lxie@ualberta.ca&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;lxie@ualberta.ca&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

